Generated runtime uses read-after-write
follow-up for create and update plus
confirm-delete for delete; `CREATING` maps to
provisioning, `UPDATING` to updating, `ACTIVE`
and `INACTIVE` to success, `DELETING` to
terminating, and `FAILED` to the terminal failed
bucket.
Pre-create lookup queries
`ListDatabaseToolsConnections` with
`compartmentId`, `displayName`, and optional
`relatedResourceIdentifier`; reusable matches
are narrowed in memory with `type`,
`connectionString` or `url`,
`relatedResource.identifier`, `userName`,
`privateEndpointId`, and `runtimeSupport`.
Only the mutable fields above reconcile in
place. `compartmentId`, `runtimeSupport`, and
`type` remain replacement-only drift even though
the provider exposes broader update paths;
post-create `locks` drift stays explicit as an
open repo-authored gap.
end note
